history.content:
CS186 is probably the most practical on that list for interviews, but it doesn't have a prof yet so you can't enrol into it as of now.

CS161 is also nice for interviews, and is a very fun class with cool projects.

DS100 is a good introduction to Data Science, might open you up to DS-based roles


EE126 is probably the least practical, at least in the short term, but will really help you strengthen your math background for something like 189.

I will have taken 61c and the other eecs lower divs by fall. I was looking around at the other posts, and I was thinking between cs161/cs186/ee126/ds100.

Does anyone know what would be a good third class, especially in terms of practicality for interviews and such?
history.subject: Third class to complement CS170 and CS188?
